      • long2IntEntrySet

        public ObjectSortedSet<Long2IntMap.Entry> long2IntEntrySet()
        Description copied from interface: Long2IntMap
        Returns a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

        This method is necessary because there is no inheritance along type parameters: it is thus impossible to strengthen Long2IntMap.entrySet() so that it returns an ObjectSet of type-specific entries (the latter makes it possible to access keys and values with type-specific methods).

        Specified by:
        long2IntEntrySet in interface Long2IntMap
        Specified by:
